snippet: Politicians and policy makers have largely overlooked people who bought insurance outside the Affordable Care Act, even though they could influence the program’s financial success.
abstract: Some health care experts estimate that millions of newly insured people decided to bypass state and federal exchanges and purchase policies directly; overlooked group will nonetheless have a significant effect on the success of the Affordable Care Act, which depends upon an influx of healthy customers to offset cost of compliance.
lead_paragraph: Politicians and policy makers have largely overlooked people who bought insurance outside the Affordable Care Act, even though they could influence the program’s financial success.
